1
00:00:14,765 --> 00:00:17,016
[Men's Choir Singing in Welsh]

2
00:01:03,731 --> 00:01:04,731
[Church Bell Ringing]

3
00:01:09,319 --> 00:01:10,778
I am packing my belongings

4
00:01:10,863 --> 00:01:14,407
in the shawl my mother
used to wear when
she went to the market,

5
00:01:14,491 --> 00:01:16,868
and I am going from my valley,

6
00:01:16,952 --> 00:01:20,580
and this time,
I shall never return.

7
00:01:20,664 --> 00:01:24,709
I am leaving behind me
my 50 years of memory.

8
00:01:24,793 --> 00:01:26,586
Memory.

9
00:01:26,670 --> 00:01:30,631
Strange that the mind will
forget so much of what only
this moment has passed

10
00:01:31,216 --> 00:01:35,094
and yet hold clear and bright
the memory of what
happened years ago,

11
00:01:35,179 --> 00:01:38,681
of men and women
long since dead.

12
00:01:38,766 --> 00:01:42,518
Yet who shall say what is real
and what is not?

13
00:01:42,603 --> 00:01:44,771
Can I believe
my friends all gone

14
00:01:44,855 --> 00:01:48,149
when their voices
are still a glory
in my ears?

15
00:01:48,692 --> 00:01:52,653
No, and I will stand
to say no and no again,

16
00:01:52,738 --> 00:01:56,073
for they remain
a living truth
within my mind.

17
00:01:56,158 --> 00:01:59,452
There is no fence
nor hedge 'round time
that is gone.

18
00:01:59,536 --> 00:02:01,162
You can go back and have
what you like of it

19
00:02:01,246 --> 00:02:02,663
if you can remember.

20
00:02:02,748 --> 00:02:05,625
So I can close my eyes
on my valley as it is today,

21
00:02:05,709 --> 00:02:09,962
and it is gone,
and I see it as it was
when I was a boy.

22
00:02:10,047 --> 00:02:13,007
Green it was
and possessed of
the plenty of the earth.

23
00:02:13,091 --> 00:02:16,969
In all Wales,
there was none so beautiful.

24
00:02:17,054 --> 00:02:21,516
Everything I ever
learnt as a small boy
came from my father,

25
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:25,520
and I never found
anything he ever told me
to be wrong or worthless.

26
00:02:25,604 --> 00:02:29,440
The simple lessons
he taught me are as sharp
and clear in my mind

27
00:02:29,525 --> 00:02:31,484
as if I had heard them
only yesterday.

28
00:02:34,238 --> 00:02:39,450
In those days, the black slag,
the waste of the coal pits,

29
00:02:39,535 --> 00:02:43,079
had only begun to cover
the side of our hill,

30
00:02:43,163 --> 00:02:45,832
not yet enough to mar
the countryside

31
00:02:45,916 --> 00:02:49,210
nor blacken the beauty
of our village,

32
00:02:49,294 --> 00:02:51,504
for the colliery
had only begun

33
00:02:51,588 --> 00:02:54,882
to poke its skinny black
fingers through the green.

34
00:02:58,345 --> 00:03:01,514
I can hear even now the voice
of my sister Angharad.

35
00:03:01,974 --> 00:03:08,521
♪ Huw ♪

36
00:03:09,606 --> 00:03:16,529
♪ Angharad ♪

37
00:03:19,783 --> 00:03:23,244
Coal miners were my father
and all my brothers,

38
00:03:23,328 --> 00:03:24,704
and proud of their trade.

39
00:03:24,788 --> 00:03:26,873
Gwilym Morgan, £3 and 7.

40
00:03:26,957 --> 00:03:28,374
Thank you, sir.

41
00:03:28,458 --> 00:03:31,252
Lanto Morgan, £3 and 7.

42
00:03:35,007 --> 00:03:37,592
Ivor Morgan, £3 and 7.

43
00:03:37,676 --> 00:03:40,094
Davy Morgan, £2 and 5.

44
00:03:42,306 --> 00:03:45,558
Owen Morgan, £2 and 5.

45
00:03:45,642 --> 00:03:49,270
Young Gwilym Morgan,
£1 and 10.

46
00:03:50,856 --> 00:03:52,899
Someone would
strike up a song,

47
00:03:52,983 --> 00:03:56,569
and the valley would ring
with the sound of many voices,

48
00:03:56,653 --> 00:04:00,239
for singing is in my people
as sight is in the eye.

49
00:04:00,490 --> 00:04:02,074
[Whistle Blows]

50
00:04:06,079 --> 00:04:07,788
[Singing in Welsh]

51
00:05:30,747 --> 00:05:33,582
Then came the scrubbing
out in the back yard.

52
00:05:34,292 --> 00:05:36,544
It was the duty
of my sister Angharad

53
00:05:36,628 --> 00:05:39,797
to bring the buckets
of hot water and cold,

54
00:05:39,881 --> 00:05:42,925
and I performed
what little tasks I could,

55
00:05:43,010 --> 00:05:47,013
as my father and brothers
scrubbed the coal dust
from their backs.

56
00:05:47,097 --> 00:05:51,017
Most would come off them,
but some would stay for life.

57
00:05:51,101 --> 00:05:53,394
This is the honorable badge
of the coal miner,

58
00:05:53,478 --> 00:05:56,439
and I envied it on my father
and grown-up brothers.

59
00:05:57,315 --> 00:05:59,316
Scrub and scrub,

60
00:05:59,401 --> 00:06:02,236
Mr. Coal would lie
there and laugh at you.

61
00:06:11,705 --> 00:06:12,788
Aah!

62
00:06:13,331 --> 00:06:14,415
Oh!

63
00:07:05,550 --> 00:07:07,760
There was always
a baron of beef

64
00:07:07,844 --> 00:07:11,972
or a shoulder or leg of lamb
before my father.

65
00:07:12,057 --> 00:07:15,267
There was never any talk
while we were eating.

66
00:07:15,352 --> 00:07:20,106
I never met anybody
whose talk was better
than good food.

67
00:07:20,190 --> 00:07:22,316
My mother
was always on the run,

68
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:26,737
always the last
to start her dinner
and the first to finish,

69
00:07:26,822 --> 00:07:31,200
for if my father
was the head of our house,
my mother was its heart.

70
00:07:33,537 --> 00:07:35,746
After dinner, when dishes
had been washed,

71
00:07:35,831 --> 00:07:37,414
the box was brought
to the table

72
00:07:37,499 --> 00:07:40,543
for the spending money
to be handed out.

73
00:07:40,627 --> 00:07:43,170
No one in our valley
had ever seen a bank.

74
00:07:43,255 --> 00:07:46,298
We kept our savings
on the mantelpiece.

75
00:07:46,383 --> 00:07:50,177
My father used to say
that money was made
to be spent,

76
00:07:50,262 --> 00:07:54,348
just as men
spend their strength
and brains in earning it,

77
00:07:54,432 --> 00:07:56,809
and as willingly,

78
00:07:56,893 --> 00:07:59,228
but always with a purpose.

79
00:08:18,832 --> 00:08:20,416
Thank you, Dada.

80
00:08:21,418 --> 00:08:23,460
Ha ha ha!

81
00:08:25,755 --> 00:08:28,174
Out of the house
and across the street,

82
00:08:28,258 --> 00:08:31,010
as I had run
a hundred times before.

83
00:08:31,094 --> 00:08:32,887
[Bell Ringing]

84
00:08:32,971 --> 00:08:37,558
Softly now, for respect
for chapel was the first
thing my father taught us.

85
00:08:41,730 --> 00:08:43,272
Then straight to Mrs. Tossall,

86
00:08:43,356 --> 00:08:47,067
the shop for that toffee
which you could
chew for hours,

87
00:08:47,152 --> 00:08:49,528
it seems to me now,

88
00:08:49,613 --> 00:08:52,156
and even after
it had gone down,

89
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:55,034
you could swallow
and still find the taste of it

90
00:08:55,118 --> 00:08:57,161
hiding behind your tongue.

91
00:08:58,830 --> 00:09:02,499
It is with me now,
so many years later.

92
00:09:02,584 --> 00:09:03,918
[Doorbell Rings]

93
00:09:04,002 --> 00:09:06,879
It makes me think of
so much that was good

94
00:09:06,963 --> 00:09:08,464
that is gone.

95
00:09:12,594 --> 00:09:16,513
It was on this afternoon
that I first saw Bron...

96
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:18,224
Bronwyn.

97
00:09:18,308 --> 00:09:20,643
She had come over
from the next valley

98
00:09:20,727 --> 00:09:23,646
for her first call
on my father and mother.

99
00:09:29,152 --> 00:09:31,403
Is this Gwilym
Morgan's house?

100
00:09:33,323 --> 00:09:34,907
You must be Huw.

101
00:09:57,097 --> 00:09:58,347
Is that you, Bronwyn?

102
00:09:59,015 --> 00:10:00,391
Yes.

103
00:10:02,769 --> 00:10:04,728
There is lovely you are.

104
00:10:05,939 --> 00:10:09,400
I think I fell in love
with Bronwyn then.

105
00:10:09,484 --> 00:10:12,861
Perhaps it is foolish to think
a child could fall in love,

106
00:10:12,946 --> 00:10:15,197
but I am the child that was,

107
00:10:15,282 --> 00:10:18,367
and nobody knows
how I felt,
except only me.

108
00:10:27,377 --> 00:10:29,837
I am so proud for Ivor.

109
00:10:29,921 --> 00:10:31,213
I'm the one
to be proud.

110
00:10:31,548 --> 00:10:33,507
You think well
of our Ivor?

111
00:10:33,591 --> 00:10:34,591
Ha ha ha!

112
00:10:34,676 --> 00:10:36,885
It seems only
a few months since he was
scratching around here

113
00:10:36,970 --> 00:10:39,388
like this one
with his mouth open.

114
00:10:43,018 --> 00:10:46,145
This is Bronwyn, Huw,
who's to be your sister.

115
00:10:46,229 --> 00:10:48,022
We have met already.

116
00:10:49,983 --> 00:10:52,901
Be careful of the basket.
There's shortcake in it.

117
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:32,691
This is not for you, Huw.
You will have your time
to come.

118
00:11:32,776 --> 00:11:34,109
Run along.

119
00:12:01,638 --> 00:12:03,514
[Singing in Welsh]

120
00:12:38,174 --> 00:12:39,258
Oh!

121
00:12:42,846 --> 00:12:46,932
Bronwyn and Ivor were
to be married by the new
preacher, Mr. Gruffydd,

122
00:12:47,016 --> 00:12:49,768
who had come from
the university at Cardiff.

123
00:12:49,853 --> 00:12:52,146
This was my first
sight of him.

124
00:13:41,154 --> 00:13:42,988
[Singing in Welsh]

125
00:13:43,072 --> 00:13:45,032
[Bell Ringing]

126
00:14:46,302 --> 00:14:47,511
Yay!
Yay!

127
00:14:48,429 --> 00:14:50,347
[Laughter]

128
00:15:06,155 --> 00:15:07,656
[Laughter Stops]

129
00:15:07,740 --> 00:15:09,074
Oh!

130
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:19,918
♪ Now, here's a man
won't get drunk ♪

131
00:15:20,003 --> 00:15:21,753
♪ Can't get drunk,
shan't get drunk ♪

132
00:15:21,838 --> 00:15:23,630
♪ Here's a man
won't get drunk ♪

133
00:15:23,715 --> 00:15:25,632
♪ Peter O'Pea ♪

134
00:15:25,717 --> 00:15:30,470
♪ From my heel to my toe
from my toe to my knee ♪

135
00:15:30,555 --> 00:15:34,516
♪ I'll walk the line,
jog the line... ♪

136
00:15:34,601 --> 00:15:35,851
♪ Oh, P... ♪

137
00:15:44,027 --> 00:15:45,235
Ohh.

138
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:46,945
Good evening,
Mr. Morgan.

139
00:15:47,030 --> 00:15:48,697
Yes, indeed, sir.

140
00:15:50,283 --> 00:15:51,325
Oh, excuse me.

141
00:15:51,409 --> 00:15:52,743
Thank you.

142
00:15:58,499 --> 00:15:59,666
Ahh.

143
00:15:59,751 --> 00:16:01,418
[Singing in Welsh]

144
00:17:09,987 --> 00:17:11,530
Come now, boys.
Back to work.

145
00:17:16,244 --> 00:17:18,537
Ivor, find Dai Griffiths
and Idris John

146
00:17:18,621 --> 00:17:20,122
and bring them
to Mr. Evans' office.

147
00:17:20,206 --> 00:17:21,540
Will we come with you?

148
00:17:21,624 --> 00:17:23,250
No. This is
for the older men.

149
00:17:23,334 --> 00:17:24,334
Home to your mother.

150
00:17:24,419 --> 00:17:25,544
But...

151
00:17:25,628 --> 00:17:27,879
Leave it now, Davy.

152
00:17:27,964 --> 00:17:29,589
Well, come! Come!

153
00:17:42,478 --> 00:17:43,645
Why aren't you washed?

154
00:17:43,730 --> 00:17:45,731
We were waiting for you.

155
00:17:49,152 --> 00:17:50,569
The cut is only
a few shillings.

156
00:17:50,653 --> 00:17:52,487
There will still be
plenty for all of us.

157
00:17:52,572 --> 00:17:54,990
A bit of supper now,
is it, girl?

158
00:17:56,659 --> 00:17:59,661
It is because
they are not getting
the old price for coal.

159
00:17:59,746 --> 00:18:00,787
Come and wash now.

160
00:18:00,872 --> 00:18:03,498
May... May we
speak first, sir?

161
00:18:04,375 --> 00:18:05,375
Yes.

162
00:18:05,668 --> 00:18:07,627
They did not give the
real reason for this cut.

163
00:18:07,712 --> 00:18:09,087
We've been expecting it

164
00:18:09,172 --> 00:18:11,506
since the ironworks
at Dowlais closed.

165
00:18:11,591 --> 00:18:13,300
What have the ironworks
to do with us?

166
00:18:13,509 --> 00:18:16,720
Their men came to the colliery
willing to work for any wage,

167
00:18:16,804 --> 00:18:18,388
so our wages
must come down.

168
00:18:18,473 --> 00:18:20,140
And this is only
the beginning.

169
00:18:20,224 --> 00:18:23,727
Watch now, they'll cut us
again and still again,

170
00:18:23,811 --> 00:18:25,854
until they have this,

171
00:18:25,938 --> 00:18:27,939
as empty
as their promises.

172
00:18:28,024 --> 00:18:30,150
Nonsense. A good worker
is worth good wages,

173
00:18:30,234 --> 00:18:32,027
and he will get them.
Not while
there are three men

174
00:18:32,111 --> 00:18:33,111
for every job.

175
00:18:33,196 --> 00:18:36,072
Why should owners pay
more if men are willing
to work for less?

176
00:18:36,157 --> 00:18:38,366
Because the owners
are not savages.

177
00:18:38,451 --> 00:18:39,701
They are men,
like us.

178
00:18:39,869 --> 00:18:41,912
Men, yes,
but not like us.

179
00:18:41,996 --> 00:18:44,122
Would they deal with you
when you went to them?

180
00:18:45,333 --> 00:18:46,291
No.

181
00:18:46,375 --> 00:18:48,293
They have power,
and we have none.

182
00:18:48,377 --> 00:18:50,504
How will we get power,
from the air?

183
00:18:50,588 --> 00:18:53,131
No. From a union
of all the men.

184
00:18:53,216 --> 00:18:54,674
Union, is it?

185
00:18:56,177 --> 00:18:59,137
I never thought
I'd hear my own sons
talking socialist nonsense.

186
00:18:59,222 --> 00:19:00,764
But it's sense,
good sense!

187
00:19:00,848 --> 00:19:01,807
Unless
we stand together...

188
00:19:01,891 --> 00:19:02,933
I've had enough
of this talk!

189
00:19:03,017 --> 00:19:04,726
But, Father, it d...

190
00:19:09,190 --> 00:19:11,566
Come and wash now.

191
00:19:11,651 --> 00:19:14,069
Your good mother
will be waiting.

192
00:19:36,175 --> 00:19:38,969
Do you think I'll let them
make my father stand
like a dog in the rain

193
00:19:39,053 --> 00:19:40,720
and not raise
my hands to stop it?

194
00:19:40,805 --> 00:19:42,222
Hisht, Davy.

195
00:19:43,599 --> 00:19:45,350
Who gave you
permission to speak?

196
00:19:45,434 --> 00:19:47,310
This is too important
for silence.

197
00:19:47,395 --> 00:19:48,436
They're trying
to punish you...

198
00:19:48,521 --> 00:19:51,356
It is not more important
than good manners.

199
00:19:53,401 --> 00:19:54,985
What are we
going to do?

200
00:19:55,069 --> 00:19:57,279
You'll die of the cold
when it comes to snow.

201
00:19:57,363 --> 00:19:59,990
Let us stand together
and see how they act then.

202
00:20:00,074 --> 00:20:04,911
Right. The men will come
if we say the word.
All the pits are ready.

203
00:20:06,289 --> 00:20:08,707
You will not make me
a plank for your politics.

204
00:20:08,791 --> 00:20:10,792
I will not be
the excuse
for any strike.

205
00:20:11,002 --> 00:20:13,545
If they can do
things like that
to the spokesman,

206
00:20:13,629 --> 00:20:14,963
what will they try
and do to the men?

207
00:20:15,381 --> 00:20:17,883
We will see.
Be silent now.
Finish your supper.

208
00:20:18,009 --> 00:20:19,968
But, Father...
Enough now!

209
00:20:20,052 --> 00:20:22,178
But...
On with your work.

210
00:20:23,598 --> 00:20:24,681
It is not enough!

211
00:20:24,765 --> 00:20:27,851
Owen! Hold your tongue until
you have permission to speak!

212
00:20:27,935 --> 00:20:31,146
I will speak against
injustice anywhere,
with permission or without it.

213
00:20:32,148 --> 00:20:33,273
Not in this house.

214
00:20:33,357 --> 00:20:35,650
In this house
and outside, sir.

215
00:20:36,819 --> 00:20:37,777
Leave the table.

216
00:20:37,862 --> 00:20:38,862
I will leave the house.

217
00:20:38,946 --> 00:20:41,239
Gwil! Tell your
father you're sorry.

218
00:20:41,324 --> 00:20:42,324
I'm not sorry.

219
00:20:43,534 --> 00:20:46,661
I am with you. We can find
lodgings in the village.

220
00:20:46,746 --> 00:20:48,204
Gwilym.

221
00:20:54,754 --> 00:20:55,837
All of you, then?

222
00:21:01,427 --> 00:21:03,595
For the last time,
sit down,
finish your supper.

223
00:21:03,679 --> 00:21:04,888
I will say no more.

224
00:21:05,181 --> 00:21:08,141
We are not questioning
your authority, sir,

225
00:21:08,225 --> 00:21:10,810
but if manners prevent
our speaking the truth,

226
00:21:10,895 --> 00:21:12,145
we will be without manners.

227
00:21:14,273 --> 00:21:15,899
Get your clothes and go.

228
00:21:32,083 --> 00:21:33,750
I am going with them
to look after them.

229
00:21:33,834 --> 00:21:36,920
Hold your tongue, girl!
Get on with your dishes!

230
00:21:45,262 --> 00:21:56,481
[Clink]

231
00:21:56,774 --> 00:21:58,233
Ah-choo!

232
00:21:58,651 --> 00:22:01,695
Yes, my son.
I know you are there.

233
00:22:55,416 --> 00:22:57,167
The men have struck.

234
00:23:02,173 --> 00:23:03,882
[Bells Ringing]

235
00:23:17,146 --> 00:23:19,481
What does it mean,
Mr. Gruffydd?

236
00:23:21,275 --> 00:23:22,734
It means that

237
00:23:25,446 --> 00:23:29,866
something has gone
out of this valley
that may never be replaced.

238
00:23:29,950 --> 00:23:33,661
Home to your
father and mother, boy.
They'll need you today.

239
00:23:54,850 --> 00:23:58,853
22 weeks the men
were out, as the strike
moved into winter.

240
00:23:59,980 --> 00:24:02,565
It was strange to go
out into the street

241
00:24:02,650 --> 00:24:05,401
and find the men there
in the daytime.

242
00:24:05,486 --> 00:24:08,571
It had a feeling
of fright in it,

243
00:24:08,656 --> 00:24:11,908
and always the mood of
the men grew uglier,

244
00:24:11,992 --> 00:24:14,285
as empty bellies
and desperation

245
00:24:14,370 --> 00:24:16,371
began to conquer reason.

246
00:24:18,415 --> 00:24:20,792
Any man who was
not their friend

247
00:24:20,876 --> 00:24:22,585
became their enemy.

248
00:24:23,504 --> 00:24:26,673
They knew that my father
had opposed the strike,

249
00:24:26,757 --> 00:24:29,300
and now it was they
who opposed him.

250
00:24:54,243 --> 00:24:55,702
[Glass Breaks]

251
00:25:05,087 --> 00:25:06,546
[Smack]

252
00:25:18,851 --> 00:25:22,395
Huw,
there's a meeting of the men
in the hills tonight, is it?

253
00:25:22,479 --> 00:25:24,230
Yes, Mama.
You will take me there.

254
00:25:24,315 --> 00:25:26,608
Oh, no, Mama.
It is no place
for women.

255
00:25:26,692 --> 00:25:30,069
There's a place
for this woman
there tonight,

256
00:25:30,154 --> 00:25:31,362
upon my soul.

257
00:25:32,156 --> 00:25:34,824
Wait, wait till you hear me.

258
00:25:34,909 --> 00:25:37,744
I am Beth Morgan,
as you damn well know.

259
00:25:38,287 --> 00:25:41,039
I have come to tell you
what I think of you all

260
00:25:41,123 --> 00:25:42,916
because you're talking
against my husband!

261
00:25:43,459 --> 00:25:46,544
You're a lot of cowards
to go against him!

262
00:25:46,629 --> 00:25:50,256
He would do
nothing against you,
and you know it well!

263
00:25:50,341 --> 00:25:53,635
How some of you,
you smug-faced hypocrites,

264
00:25:53,719 --> 00:25:56,930
can sit in the same chapel
with him I cannot tell.

265
00:25:57,848 --> 00:26:00,183
To say he's with the owners
is not only nonsense,

266
00:26:00,267 --> 00:26:01,768
but downright wickedness!

267
00:26:01,977 --> 00:26:05,230
There's one thing
more I've got to say,
and it is this,

268
00:26:05,314 --> 00:26:10,068
if harm comes to my Gwilym,
I'll find out the men,

269
00:26:10,152 --> 00:26:13,571
and I will kill them
with my two hands,

270
00:26:13,656 --> 00:26:16,824
and this I will swear
by God Almighty!

271
00:26:29,004 --> 00:26:30,713
[Murmuring]

272
00:26:53,570 --> 00:26:56,114
Lanto, help!

273
00:26:56,198 --> 00:26:57,532
Help!

274
00:27:00,035 --> 00:27:02,495
Help! Help!

275
00:27:03,956 --> 00:27:07,125
Hold on, Mama!
They've heard us!
They're coming!

276
00:27:45,372 --> 00:27:46,497
Ahh.

277
00:27:50,419 --> 00:27:51,836
He was awake just now.

278
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:53,171
Shh.

279
00:27:56,592 --> 00:27:58,009
He'll do, then.

280
00:27:58,093 --> 00:28:00,553
But it's beyond me
to say why!

281
00:28:02,181 --> 00:28:05,433
You're breeding horses
in this family, Mr. Morgan.

282
00:28:05,559 --> 00:28:06,726
Ha!

283
00:28:06,810 --> 00:28:10,438
This boy should be in
his coffin, for my part.

284
00:28:10,522 --> 00:28:11,856
He's a Morgan,
then, is it, sir?

285
00:28:11,940 --> 00:28:13,232
Eh.

286
00:28:14,068 --> 00:28:16,694
He should be fed
now, Mrs. Ivor,

287
00:28:16,779 --> 00:28:22,116
a little soup
and some warm smile.

288
00:28:23,619 --> 00:28:25,953
Ahhh.

289
00:28:27,081 --> 00:28:28,456
Yes.

290
00:28:31,543 --> 00:28:32,710
Ah!

291
00:28:32,795 --> 00:28:34,212
Horse!

292
00:28:35,631 --> 00:28:37,548
Well, good day.
Wait, wait, wait.

293
00:28:37,633 --> 00:28:39,717
Huw was awake.
He spoke to Bron.

294
00:28:39,802 --> 00:28:41,427
How long for
the little one?

295
00:28:41,512 --> 00:28:42,970
It's hard to tell.

296
00:28:43,055 --> 00:28:44,722
His legs were frozen
to the bone.

297
00:28:44,807 --> 00:28:47,183
A year,
two year like that,

298
00:28:47,267 --> 00:28:49,894
but I can't promise
he'll ever walk again!

299
00:28:49,978 --> 00:28:52,146
Nature must
take her course!

300
00:28:53,607 --> 00:28:55,483
Mind your tongue!

301
00:28:55,567 --> 00:28:57,193
I think he heard you.

302
00:29:16,171 --> 00:29:19,298
Where is the light
I thought to see in your eye?

303
00:29:22,010 --> 00:29:23,803
Are you afraid, boy?

304
00:29:24,638 --> 00:29:25,680
Hmm?

305
00:29:31,061 --> 00:29:33,104
You heard what
the doctor said?

306
00:29:33,188 --> 00:29:34,689
Yes, sir.

307
00:29:34,773 --> 00:29:37,775
And you believed it?

308
00:29:37,860 --> 00:29:39,110
Yes, sir.

309
00:29:41,029 --> 00:29:43,906
You want to walk again,
don't you?

310
00:29:43,991 --> 00:29:45,241
Yes, sir.

311
00:29:46,994 --> 00:29:49,412
Then you must have faith,

312
00:29:49,496 --> 00:29:51,330
and if you have,
you will walk again

313
00:29:51,415 --> 00:29:53,875
no matter what
all the doctors say.

314
00:29:55,461 --> 00:29:59,338
But he said nature
must take her course.

315
00:30:02,009 --> 00:30:04,719
"Nature is
the handmaiden
of the Lord."

316
00:30:06,513 --> 00:30:08,264
I remember one
or two occasions

317
00:30:08,390 --> 00:30:11,392
when she was given orders
to change her course.

318
00:30:11,477 --> 00:30:13,978
You know your
scriptures, boy.

319
00:30:14,062 --> 00:30:15,229
Yes, sir.

320
00:30:15,314 --> 00:30:17,482
Then you know that
what's been done before

321
00:30:17,566 --> 00:30:20,193
can be done again,
for you.

322
00:30:21,528 --> 00:30:23,404
Do you believe me, Huw?

323
00:30:24,406 --> 00:30:25,406
Yes, sir.

324
00:30:25,491 --> 00:30:27,158
Good.

325
00:30:27,242 --> 00:30:30,620
You will see
the first daffodil
out on the mountain.

326
00:30:30,746 --> 00:30:32,413
Will you?

327
00:30:32,498 --> 00:30:34,248
Indeed I will, sir.

328
00:30:34,750 --> 00:30:36,417
Then you will.

329
00:30:40,589 --> 00:30:43,090
I could almost wish

330
00:30:43,175 --> 00:30:46,385
that I were lying
there in your place,

331
00:30:46,470 --> 00:30:49,931
if it meant
reading this book again
for the first time.

332
00:30:51,225 --> 00:30:54,519
Treasure Island.

333
00:31:23,799 --> 00:31:25,299
Mr. Gruffydd?

334
00:31:27,302 --> 00:31:30,096
I couldn't let you go
without thanking you.

335
00:31:30,180 --> 00:31:31,639
It was only my duty, girl.

336
00:31:31,723 --> 00:31:33,975
No. It was more than duty.

337
00:31:35,102 --> 00:31:39,146
Yes, Huw's a fine boy,
and you're a fine family.

338
00:31:40,649 --> 00:31:42,984
Um, you'd better be
going in now. You'll
catch your death.

339
00:31:43,068 --> 00:31:44,151
Yes.

340
00:31:45,320 --> 00:31:47,113
Will you be
coming to supper soon?

341
00:31:47,489 --> 00:31:50,408
Uh, yes, later,

342
00:31:50,492 --> 00:31:52,493
when you're finished
with doctors and such, huh?

343
00:31:53,662 --> 00:31:54,912
I will hurry them away, then.

344
00:31:54,997 --> 00:31:56,163
Good.

345
00:32:02,254 --> 00:32:04,422
"Squire Trelawney,
Dr. Livesey,

346
00:32:04,506 --> 00:32:06,132
"and the rest
of these gentlemen,

347
00:32:06,216 --> 00:32:10,678
having asked me to write down
the whole particulars
about Treasure Island

348
00:32:14,683 --> 00:32:16,309
from the beginning
to the end,

349
00:32:16,643 --> 00:32:19,270
keeping nothing back but
the bearings of the island,

350
00:32:19,354 --> 00:32:22,607
and that only because
there is still treasure
not yet lifted,

351
00:32:22,691 --> 00:32:26,861
I take up my pen
in the year of grace 1785,

352
00:32:33,118 --> 00:32:34,368
and go back to the time

353
00:32:34,453 --> 00:32:37,371
when my father kept
the Admiral Benbow Inn..."

354
00:32:39,958 --> 00:32:44,545
All the noble books
which have lived in
my mind ever since,

355
00:32:44,630 --> 00:32:47,214
and always I hoped
and kept my faith.

356
00:32:48,300 --> 00:32:49,800
For the first months,

357
00:32:49,885 --> 00:32:51,802
my mother was still upstairs,

358
00:32:51,887 --> 00:32:54,889
and we could talk
to each other with tappings.

359
00:33:18,205 --> 00:33:24,085
[Chirp]

360
00:33:38,767 --> 00:33:40,226
[Huw Whistling]

361
00:33:44,272 --> 00:33:46,232
[Cackling]

362
00:34:01,498 --> 00:34:02,623
Spring?

363
00:34:15,971 --> 00:34:17,763
There you are, girl.

364
00:34:20,142 --> 00:34:21,225
Easy.

365
00:34:22,686 --> 00:34:24,186
There you are.

366
00:34:26,606 --> 00:34:27,690
Wait.

367
00:34:41,163 --> 00:34:43,456
It's the old snow got into it.

368
00:34:49,713 --> 00:34:53,340
[Singing in Welsh]

369
00:35:48,438 --> 00:35:49,814
Oh, Gwilym.

370
00:35:51,149 --> 00:35:52,817
There is a wife you have,

371
00:35:52,901 --> 00:35:57,071
resting in her bed
and letting strangers
care for her family.

372
00:35:57,197 --> 00:35:59,281
There is a wife
I have, then.

373
00:35:59,366 --> 00:36:01,408
Go along with you, boy.

374
00:36:06,998 --> 00:36:10,251
[Singing in Welsh]

375
00:37:13,106 --> 00:37:14,648
Will you say something,
Mother?

376
00:37:17,861 --> 00:37:19,361
Go on. Say something.

377
00:37:19,446 --> 00:37:21,864
But what...
What'll I say?

378
00:37:23,867 --> 00:37:26,118
You found plenty to say
the last time you spoke.

379
00:37:26,202 --> 00:37:28,829
It should be easier now,
with friends.

380
00:37:31,666 --> 00:37:33,000
Well...

381
00:37:34,294 --> 00:37:37,338
Well, come and eat,
everyone.

382
00:37:45,138 --> 00:37:47,056
Smoke is it, boys.

383
00:37:56,650 --> 00:37:58,776
Lanto.

384
00:37:58,860 --> 00:38:01,612
I haven't seen you
in chapel lately.

385
00:38:01,696 --> 00:38:03,238
I have been too busy.

386
00:38:03,323 --> 00:38:05,449
What business,
may I ask?

387
00:38:05,533 --> 00:38:06,951
Mine.

388
00:38:07,035 --> 00:38:09,787
Only asking
a civil question, I was.

389
00:38:09,871 --> 00:38:11,747
And having
a civil answer.

390
00:38:11,831 --> 00:38:14,416
I have been busy
with the union.

391
00:38:14,501 --> 00:38:17,211
Unions are the work
of the devil.

392
00:38:17,295 --> 00:38:19,296
You will come
to no good end.

393
00:38:19,381 --> 00:38:22,466
At least
I am not sitting on it,
talking rubbish in chapel.

394
00:38:22,550 --> 00:38:24,009
Look here...
Oh, leave it,

395
00:38:24,094 --> 00:38:25,594
or I'll say something
to be sorry.

396
00:38:26,805 --> 00:38:30,432
This is a matter
that requires airing.

397
00:38:30,517 --> 00:38:35,020
Lanto, why do you think
we at the chapel talk rubbish?

398
00:38:35,105 --> 00:38:38,148
My remark was
not aimed at you.

399
00:38:38,233 --> 00:38:39,650
Then aim it.

400
00:38:41,653 --> 00:38:42,987
Very well.

401
00:38:45,198 --> 00:38:49,827
Because you make
yourselves out to be
shepherds of the flock,

402
00:38:49,911 --> 00:38:54,373
and yet you allow your sheep
to live in filth and poverty,

403
00:38:54,457 --> 00:38:57,751
and if they try
and raise their
voices against it,

404
00:38:57,836 --> 00:39:02,047
you calm them by telling
them their suffering
is the will of God.

405
00:39:03,425 --> 00:39:05,509
Sheep, indeed.

406
00:39:05,593 --> 00:39:09,388
Are we sheep to be
herded and sheared
by a handful of owners?

407
00:39:11,016 --> 00:39:15,519
I was taught man
was made in the image
of God, not a sheep.

408
00:39:15,603 --> 00:39:18,689
I haven't expressed
my views around here

409
00:39:18,773 --> 00:39:23,652
because I haven't had
any wish to interfere
in a family disagreement.

410
00:39:23,737 --> 00:39:26,780
You have
my permission
to speak.

411
00:39:26,865 --> 00:39:30,200
Very well, then.
Here is what I think.

412
00:39:30,285 --> 00:39:32,494
First, have your union.

413
00:39:33,413 --> 00:39:34,747
You need it.

414
00:39:34,831 --> 00:39:38,292
Alone, you are weak.
Together, you're strong.

415
00:39:38,376 --> 00:39:41,545
But remember
that with strength
goes responsibility,

416
00:39:41,629 --> 00:39:43,714
to others
and yourselves,

417
00:39:43,798 --> 00:39:47,509
for you cannot conquer
injustice with more injustice,

418
00:39:47,594 --> 00:39:50,012
only with justice
and the help of God.

419
00:39:50,096 --> 00:39:53,849
Are you coming outside
your position in life,
Mr. Gruffydd?

420
00:39:54,142 --> 00:39:56,226
Your business
is spiritual.

421
00:39:56,311 --> 00:39:59,605
My business is anything
that comes between man
and the spirit of God.

422
00:39:59,689 --> 00:40:03,400
The deacons shall hear
that you've been
preaching socialism!

423
00:40:03,485 --> 00:40:04,485
Mr. Parry!

424
00:40:04,569 --> 00:40:05,986
Loose the old devil's teeth!

425
00:40:06,112 --> 00:40:08,155
He is our guest!

426
00:40:08,239 --> 00:40:10,365
Beth, a pint
of home brew
for Mr. Parry.

427
00:40:10,450 --> 00:40:12,868
I'll give him a clout
with a frying pan!

428
00:40:12,952 --> 00:40:13,994
Oh!

429
00:40:14,829 --> 00:40:17,498
Miss Jenkins!
A sweet song!
The harp, is it?

430
00:40:17,582 --> 00:40:18,999
Come on, men.
Get in here.

431
00:40:19,084 --> 00:40:21,168
Now, look.
A little song...

432
00:40:38,895 --> 00:40:40,813
Angharad.

433
00:40:40,897 --> 00:40:43,982
Mr. Gruffydd,
will we always be
in your debt,

434
00:40:44,067 --> 00:40:46,610
now you have made
us a family again?

435
00:40:48,655 --> 00:40:50,155
Here. Let me.

436
00:41:01,668 --> 00:41:02,709
Oh, your hands.

437
00:41:03,545 --> 00:41:04,545
There's a pity.

438
00:41:04,629 --> 00:41:05,963
No matter.

439
00:41:10,009 --> 00:41:12,302
Have you ever been
down the collieries?

440
00:41:12,387 --> 00:41:13,804
10 years.

441
00:41:13,888 --> 00:41:14,972
10 years?

442
00:41:15,056 --> 00:41:16,974
While I was studying.

443
00:41:19,394 --> 00:41:20,811
A bit of soap now.

444
00:41:20,895 --> 00:41:22,896
Oh, don't bother,
please.

445
00:41:26,067 --> 00:41:29,528
There's a man
for you, spoiling
his good handkerchief.

446
00:41:30,780 --> 00:41:33,866
Look, now,
you are king
in the chapel,

447
00:41:33,950 --> 00:41:36,076
but I will be queen
in my own kitchen.

448
00:41:36,161 --> 00:41:38,704
You will be queen
wherever you walk.

449
00:41:41,457 --> 00:41:43,250
What does that mean?

450
00:41:44,252 --> 00:41:46,753
I should not
have said it.

451
00:41:46,838 --> 00:41:47,921
Why?

452
00:41:50,592 --> 00:41:54,052
I have no right
to speak to you so.

453
00:41:58,933 --> 00:42:00,392
Mr. Gruffydd?

454
00:42:03,104 --> 00:42:06,982
If the right is mine to give,

455
00:42:07,066 --> 00:42:08,442
you have it.

456
00:42:22,707 --> 00:42:24,541
[Horn Blowing]

457
00:42:26,794 --> 00:42:28,587
Then the strike was settled,

458
00:42:28,671 --> 00:42:31,673
with the help
of Mr. Gruffydd
and my father.

459
00:42:31,758 --> 00:42:33,217
Work again,

460
00:42:33,301 --> 00:42:37,137
work to wipe out the memory
of idleness and hardship.

461
00:42:37,222 --> 00:42:39,306
The men were happy going
up the hill that morning.

462
00:42:40,433 --> 00:42:42,017
1 and 9.
1 and 9.

463
00:42:42,101 --> 00:42:43,518
1 and 10!

464
00:42:43,645 --> 00:42:45,562
[Horn Blowing]

465
00:42:48,650 --> 00:42:50,317
But not all of them,

466
00:42:50,401 --> 00:42:53,028
for there were too many now
for the jobs open,

467
00:42:53,112 --> 00:42:55,280
and some learned
that never again

468
00:42:55,365 --> 00:42:58,533
would there be work for them
in their own valley.

469
00:43:14,842 --> 00:43:18,428
It is the same all over
South Wales, it is.

470
00:43:18,513 --> 00:43:19,638
Father.

471
00:43:19,722 --> 00:43:24,393
In Cardiff, the men are
standing in line to have
bread from the government.

472
00:43:24,477 --> 00:43:26,645
Not for us, eh, lad?

473
00:43:30,525 --> 00:43:33,110
We will have our
share of the box

474
00:43:33,194 --> 00:43:35,070
and go,
if you please, sir.

475
00:43:35,863 --> 00:43:37,614
Where will you go?

476
00:43:37,699 --> 00:43:38,699
America.

477
00:43:53,798 --> 00:43:54,965
My share, too, Owen.

478
00:43:55,049 --> 00:43:56,216
And mine.

479
00:43:56,301 --> 00:43:58,260
No. Our own.

480
00:43:59,304 --> 00:44:01,013
We will take
no charity.

481
00:44:01,097 --> 00:44:03,181
Not charity, man, sense.

482
00:44:03,391 --> 00:44:05,058
No, only our own.

483
00:44:06,227 --> 00:44:07,227
Ahem.

484
00:44:07,312 --> 00:44:08,812
[Sniff Sniff]

485
00:44:09,731 --> 00:44:12,816
Say nothing of this
to your mother.

486
00:44:12,900 --> 00:44:14,985
Let this day
be over first.

487
00:44:15,069 --> 00:44:16,611
Never mind
saying nothing.

488
00:44:17,780 --> 00:44:19,072
I heard.

489
00:44:24,203 --> 00:44:26,121
America?

490
00:44:27,123 --> 00:44:28,749
My babies.

491
00:44:42,221 --> 00:44:44,598
Shall we have a chapter,
my sons?

492
00:44:50,521 --> 00:44:53,690
What shall
we have, sir?

493
00:44:53,775 --> 00:44:55,609
Isaiah 55.

494
00:44:57,403 --> 00:44:58,695
Those two gone,

495
00:44:58,780 --> 00:44:59,946
this is only
the beginning.

496
00:45:00,031 --> 00:45:03,283
Then all of you will go.
One after the other,
all of you.

497
00:45:03,368 --> 00:45:05,535
I will never
leave you, Mama.

498
00:45:05,620 --> 00:45:08,497
Huw, boy, if you
should ever leave me,

499
00:45:08,581 --> 00:45:11,208
I'll be sorry
I ever had babies.

500
00:45:11,292 --> 00:45:13,126
Why did you
have them?

501
00:45:15,296 --> 00:45:17,714
Indeed to goodness,
boy, why?

502
00:45:17,799 --> 00:45:21,468
To keep my hands in water
and my face to the fire,
perhaps.

503
00:45:31,604 --> 00:45:32,938
Whoa!

504
00:45:42,198 --> 00:45:44,074
For Mr. Ivor Morgan.

505
00:45:46,536 --> 00:45:48,995
From Windsor Castle it is.

506
00:46:23,531 --> 00:46:27,325
"Mr. Ivor Morgan is
commanded to appear
before Her Majest..."

507
00:46:29,036 --> 00:46:31,163
"Mr. Ivor Morgan
is commanded

508
00:46:31,247 --> 00:46:33,832
to appear before
Her Majesty
at Windsor Castle

509
00:46:33,916 --> 00:46:36,585
with chosen members
of his choir
the 14th of May

510
