See? Ha ha!

577
00:51:17,575 --> 00:51:19,701
There's a good old man.

578
00:51:24,707 --> 00:51:27,125
You've been lucky, Huw.

579
00:51:27,209 --> 00:51:29,919
Lucky to suffer,

580
00:51:30,004 --> 00:51:33,882
lucky to spend these
weary months in bed.

581
00:51:33,966 --> 00:51:36,426
For so God has
given you a chance

582
00:51:36,510 --> 00:51:39,429
to make spirit
within yourself,

583
00:51:39,513 --> 00:51:42,974
and as your father
cleans his lamp
to have good light,

584
00:51:43,934 --> 00:51:46,561
so keep clean
your spirit, huh?

585
00:51:46,645 --> 00:51:47,896
How, sir?

586
00:51:52,318 --> 00:51:54,944
By prayer, Huw.

587
00:51:55,029 --> 00:51:58,156
And by prayer,
I don't mean
shouting and mumbling

588
00:51:58,240 --> 00:52:02,202
and wallowing like a hog
in religious sentiment.

589
00:52:02,286 --> 00:52:07,165
Prayer is only
another name for good,
clean, direct thinking.

590
00:52:08,959 --> 00:52:11,211
When you pray, think.

591
00:52:12,129 --> 00:52:14,214
Think well
what you're saying.

592
00:52:14,298 --> 00:52:17,425
Make your thoughts into
things that are solid,

593
00:52:17,510 --> 00:52:20,887
and that way,
your prayer will
have strength,

594
00:52:20,971 --> 00:52:23,181
and that strength will
become a part of you,

595
00:52:23,265 --> 00:52:27,185
body, mind,
and spirit.

596
00:52:27,269 --> 00:52:30,104
And the first duty
of these new legs

597
00:52:30,189 --> 00:52:33,316
is to get you
to chapel on Sunday.

598
00:52:33,400 --> 00:52:35,735
Indeed they will, sir.

599
00:52:35,820 --> 00:52:37,695
There's a good
old man again.

600
00:52:40,491 --> 00:52:42,158
Give me your hand.

601
00:52:49,583 --> 00:52:50,959
Come on now.

602
