750
01:06:36,910 --> 01:06:41,497
"A" fills it at the rate
of 20 gallons a minute

751
01:06:42,707 --> 01:06:46,418
and "B" at the rate
of 10 gallons a minute.

752
01:06:46,503 --> 01:06:48,003
Got that, Mr. Morgan?

753
01:06:48,088 --> 01:06:50,381
20 and 10 gallons.
Yes, sir.

754
01:06:50,465 --> 01:06:51,674
Now, then,

755
01:06:51,758 --> 01:06:55,761
"C" is a hole that empties it
at the rate of 5
gallons a minute.

756
01:06:56,638 --> 01:06:59,848
How long to fill the tub?

757
01:07:01,101 --> 01:07:02,101
Hmm.

758
01:07:02,936 --> 01:07:04,395
Ha ha ha!

759
01:07:05,313 --> 01:07:06,355
They're silly.

760
01:07:06,439 --> 01:07:09,233
Trying to fill a bathtub
full of holes, indeed.

761
01:07:09,943 --> 01:07:13,112
A sum it is, girl, a sum,
a problem for the mind,

762
01:07:13,571 --> 01:07:15,614
for his examination
into school next month.

763
01:07:15,699 --> 01:07:19,243
That old national school,
just silly they are with
their sums.

764
01:07:19,327 --> 01:07:21,370
Who would pour water
in a bathtub full of holes?

765
01:07:21,454 --> 01:07:23,330
Who would think of it?
Only a madman.

766
01:07:23,415 --> 01:07:25,708
It is to see if the boy
can calculate, girl.

767
01:07:25,792 --> 01:07:27,209
Figures, nothing else.

768
01:07:27,293 --> 01:07:29,169
How many gallons
and how long?

769
01:07:29,713 --> 01:07:32,297
In a bathtub
full of holes.

770
01:07:34,801 --> 01:07:37,803
Now I know why I have
such a tribe of sons.

771
01:07:37,887 --> 01:07:41,181
It is you,
Beth Morgan,
is the cause.

772
01:07:41,266 --> 01:07:44,143
Look you, Mr. Gruffydd,
have you something else?

773
01:07:44,227 --> 01:07:49,148
The decimal point.

774
01:07:50,567 --> 01:07:52,568
The decimal point, then.

775
01:07:52,652 --> 01:07:53,902
And peace to my house!

776
01:07:53,987 --> 01:07:55,362
Go and scratch.

777
01:07:55,447 --> 01:07:57,740
Uh, it's getting late.
I've got to get along.

778
01:07:57,824 --> 01:07:59,658
We'll follow
the decimal point
tomorrow night.

779
01:07:59,743 --> 01:08:01,368
Yes, sir.
Good night.

780
01:08:01,453 --> 01:08:02,578
Good night,
Mrs. Morgan.

781
01:08:02,662 --> 01:08:04,329
Good night, Mr. Gruffydd.

782
01:08:06,624 --> 01:08:08,250
Who is there that
cannot look back

783
01:08:08,334 --> 01:08:11,462
and remember his first day
at a new school?

784
01:08:11,546 --> 01:08:14,214
To go alone the long
walk over the hills

785
01:08:14,340 --> 01:08:16,049
to the next valley,

786
01:08:16,134 --> 01:08:18,594
the first of my family
to have the privilege

787
01:08:18,678 --> 01:08:20,721
of attending
a national school.

788
01:08:58,051 --> 01:08:59,968
So you're the new boy?

789
01:09:01,554 --> 01:09:03,430
Yes, sir.
You're late.

790
01:09:05,225 --> 01:09:06,308
Yes, sir.

791
01:09:07,977 --> 01:09:10,312
What a dirty
little sweep it is.

792
01:09:10,438 --> 01:09:12,064
[Laughter]

793
01:09:12,148 --> 01:09:13,190
Who are your people?

794
01:09:14,234 --> 01:09:15,400
Where are you from?

795
01:09:15,527 --> 01:09:16,568
Cwm Rhondda.

796
01:09:17,403 --> 01:09:18,821
Cwm Rhondda?

797
01:09:20,073 --> 01:09:24,117
Oh, a little genius
from the coal pits,

798
01:09:24,202 --> 01:09:25,869
and they expect me to
make a scholar of it.

799
01:09:26,246 --> 01:09:27,955
All right, come in.

800
01:09:32,919 --> 01:09:34,545
Were you
brought up in stables?

801
01:09:34,629 --> 01:09:35,629
[Laughter]

802
01:09:35,713 --> 01:09:36,922
Well, shut the door.

803
01:10:08,454 --> 01:10:09,872
[Laughter]

804
01:10:12,166 --> 01:10:13,959
Your boots are muddy.

805
01:10:17,046 --> 01:10:18,630
They were clean
when I left home.

806
01:10:20,300 --> 01:10:23,635
You will address me
as sir, or I'll put
a stick about your back.

807
01:10:23,720 --> 01:10:25,512
Now, sit down here.

808
01:10:25,597 --> 01:10:26,847
Yes, sir.

809
01:10:35,732 --> 01:10:37,024
Ha ha ha!

810
01:10:38,192 --> 01:10:39,651
[Laughter]

811
01:10:56,878 --> 01:10:59,087
Come here,
you dirty little sweep.

812
01:11:01,591 --> 01:11:04,217
What have we here?

813
01:11:04,302 --> 01:11:06,595
A pencil box.

814
01:11:06,679 --> 01:11:08,013
Pretty, too.

815
01:11:13,269 --> 01:11:15,479
Hey, you broke
my pencil box!

816
01:11:18,691 --> 01:11:20,609
[Shrieking]

817
01:11:24,197 --> 01:11:26,657
Mervyn, Mervyn, stop it!
You'll hurt him!

818
01:11:29,953 --> 01:11:32,955
Hit him! Hit him!

819
01:12:01,943 --> 01:12:04,569
I... I fell
on the mountain.

820
01:12:08,408 --> 01:12:10,033
Did you win, Huw?

821
01:12:11,411 --> 01:12:12,536
No.

822
01:12:15,415 --> 01:12:16,581
Lanto!

823
01:12:29,554 --> 01:12:31,221
Fetch Dai Bando.

824
01:12:31,305 --> 01:12:32,931
Dai Bando, is it?

825
01:12:59,959 --> 01:13:02,377
Are you willing to go
to school tomorrow?

826
01:13:02,462 --> 01:13:04,421
Yes, sir.
Good.

827
01:13:04,505 --> 01:13:07,382
From tonight,
you shall get a penny for
every mark on your face,

828
01:13:07,467 --> 01:13:10,177
sixpence for a bloody nose,
a shilling for a black eye,

829
01:13:10,261 --> 01:13:11,887
and two shillings
for a broken nose.

830
01:13:11,971 --> 01:13:13,555
Gwilym, stop it.

831
01:13:13,848 --> 01:13:15,891
Fight again,
and when you come home,

832
01:13:15,975 --> 01:13:17,476
not another look
will you get from me,

833
01:13:17,560 --> 01:13:19,019
not another word.

834
01:13:19,103 --> 01:13:20,395
Break your own nose, then.

835
01:13:21,147 --> 01:13:23,231
Break your mother's heart.

836
01:13:23,316 --> 01:13:25,275
A boy must fight, Beth.

837
01:13:25,359 --> 01:13:27,611
Fight? Fight, is it?

838
01:13:27,695 --> 01:13:29,488
Another beating like that
and he would walk home dead.

839
01:13:29,697 --> 01:13:31,990
Beating?
He's had no beating.

840
01:13:32,075 --> 01:13:33,992
A hiding, yes,
but no beating.

841
01:13:34,077 --> 01:13:38,205
Give the boy time, it will be
he that's giving the beating,
is it?

842
01:13:38,289 --> 01:13:40,582
Dai Bando,
come into the house.

843
01:13:41,834 --> 01:13:43,585
Good evening, Mrs. Morgan.
Good Evening, Mrs. Morgan.

844
01:13:43,669 --> 01:13:45,420
Leave off your hat.

845
01:13:58,768 --> 01:14:01,436
Dai Bando is going
to teach you to box, Huw.

846
01:14:01,521 --> 01:14:02,771
To fight first.

847
01:14:02,855 --> 01:14:05,816
Too many call themselves
boxers who are not even
fighters.

848
01:14:05,900 --> 01:14:07,067
Boxing is an art, is it?

849
01:14:07,318 --> 01:14:09,778
It is. It is.

850
01:14:09,862 --> 01:14:12,447
Go along with you, girl.
A cup of tea for the men,
is it?

851
01:14:12,532 --> 01:14:13,532
Tea?

852
01:14:13,616 --> 01:14:17,202
Tea? No tea, Mrs. Morgan.

853
01:14:17,787 --> 01:14:20,622
In training, he is.

854
01:14:20,706 --> 01:14:23,750
A glass of beer
if you please.

855
01:14:26,671 --> 01:14:29,548
Baths full of holes,

856
01:14:29,674 --> 01:14:31,883
and now prizefighters.

857
01:14:31,968 --> 01:14:33,510
Get him!
Come on!

858
01:14:33,594 --> 01:14:34,594
Get him!

859
01:14:34,679 --> 01:14:35,971
Come on, get him, Mervyn!

860
01:14:51,028 --> 01:14:53,822
Get up! Get up!

861
01:14:53,948 --> 01:14:55,157
Hit him!

862
01:14:55,575 --> 01:14:57,576
Knock him down, Mervyn!

863
01:14:57,660 --> 01:14:59,286
Hit him, Mervyn!

864
01:15:04,750 --> 01:15:07,127
Our wild little
coal-mining friend
has been indulging

865
01:15:07,211 --> 01:15:08,670
in his favorite
sport again, eh?

866
01:15:08,754 --> 01:15:09,796
Mr. Phillips,
make a back, please.

867
01:15:09,881 --> 01:15:10,881
I refuse, sir.

868
01:15:10,923 --> 01:15:12,841
Make a back,
Mr. Phillips!
I refuse, sir!

869
01:15:12,925 --> 01:15:14,843
Mr. Mills,
make a back.

870
01:15:18,264 --> 01:15:21,266
Here. Put this in
between your teeth.

871
01:15:21,726 --> 01:15:23,185
Bite it hard.

872
01:15:44,290 --> 01:15:45,957
Well, the scholar!

873
01:15:51,589 --> 01:15:53,506
[Whimpering]

874
01:16:03,100 --> 01:16:04,226
Huw!
Lad!

875
01:16:04,310 --> 01:16:06,144
I'll go to my death.

876
01:16:07,188 --> 01:16:08,313
You got that in school?

877
01:16:08,397 --> 01:16:10,732
He's cut you to the bone.
Who was it?

878
01:16:10,816 --> 01:16:11,775
Mr. Jonas?

879
01:16:11,859 --> 01:16:13,318
We'll have a word
with him.

880
01:16:13,402 --> 01:16:14,402
No.

881
01:16:14,487 --> 01:16:15,570
Why not?

882
01:16:15,655 --> 01:16:17,030
I broke the rule
when I fought.

883
01:16:17,114 --> 01:16:19,115
There's no rule
for that.

884
01:16:19,200 --> 01:16:20,659
But he warned me.

885
01:16:20,743 --> 01:16:22,369
Rubbish, boy!
Wait, Davy.

886
01:16:23,996 --> 01:16:26,665
This is Huw's affair.
He shall decide.

887
01:16:27,625 --> 01:16:31,169
Say the word, lad,
and we will have the
bones hot from his flesh.

888
01:16:31,254 --> 01:16:33,672
No. Leave him alone.

889
01:16:37,218 --> 01:16:40,387
I think our baby brother
is becoming quite a man.

890
01:17:05,538 --> 01:17:07,789
These denominations

891
01:17:07,873 --> 01:17:10,875
are used in measuring
distances and...

892
01:17:12,545 --> 01:17:13,962
Yes?
Right!

893
01:17:17,967 --> 01:17:18,967
Good morning,
Mister...

894
01:17:19,051 --> 01:17:20,010
Jonas.

895
01:17:20,094 --> 01:17:22,220
Mr. Jonas.
Mr. Jonas.

896
01:17:22,305 --> 01:17:24,681
We have come to
the right place, indeed.

897
01:17:24,765 --> 01:17:26,057
Ha ha ha!

898
01:17:26,934 --> 01:17:28,393
What can I
do for you?

899
01:17:28,477 --> 01:17:33,189
A man is never
too old to learn,
is it, Mr. Jonas?

900
01:17:33,274 --> 01:17:34,274
No.

901
01:17:34,358 --> 01:17:35,900
I was in school
myself once,

902
01:17:36,277 --> 01:17:37,861
but no great one
for knowledge.

903
01:17:37,945 --> 01:17:40,113
Look here,
what do you want?

904
01:17:40,239 --> 01:17:41,573
Knowledge.

905
01:17:42,408 --> 01:17:44,659
How would you go about

906
01:17:44,744 --> 01:17:48,997
taking the measurement
of a stick, Mr. Jonas?

907
01:17:49,081 --> 01:17:50,874
By its length, of course.

908
01:17:50,958 --> 01:17:52,417
And how would you
measure a man

909
01:17:52,501 --> 01:17:55,337
who would use a stick
on a boy 1/3 his size?

910
01:17:55,421 --> 01:17:56,671
Tell us.

911
01:17:57,465 --> 01:17:59,424
Now, you are good
in the use of a stick,

912
01:17:59,633 --> 01:18:01,092
but boxing
is my subject,

913
01:18:01,177 --> 01:18:04,346
according to the rules
laid down by the good
Marquis of Queensberry.

914
01:18:04,430 --> 01:18:06,681
God rest his soul.

915
01:18:07,767 --> 01:18:11,269
And happy I am to pass
on my knowledge to you.

916
01:18:14,106 --> 01:18:17,067
Mr. Motshill!

917
01:18:17,151 --> 01:18:19,110
All right, get him
into position, now.

918
01:18:19,195 --> 01:18:22,030
Now, look,
to make a good boxer,

919
01:18:22,114 --> 01:18:25,241
you must have a good
right hand, you see?

920
01:18:27,953 --> 01:18:30,205
Now, you see,
that is how you
will punish your man,

921
01:18:30,289 --> 01:18:33,500
with a right
and a left.

922
01:18:33,584 --> 01:18:36,503
The gentleman
is talking to you.

923
01:18:37,922 --> 01:18:38,880
Raise him.

924
01:18:38,964 --> 01:18:40,757
Come on, come on.
Up, up, up.

925
01:18:40,841 --> 01:18:42,384
Position again.

926
01:18:43,636 --> 01:18:45,470
Could I have your attention,
boys and girls?

927
01:18:49,183 --> 01:18:51,643
I am not accustomed
to speaking in public.

928
01:18:51,727 --> 01:18:52,894
Only public houses.

929
01:18:52,978 --> 01:18:56,189
But this, never use.

930
01:18:56,273 --> 01:18:57,607
It's against the rules.

931
01:18:57,691 --> 01:19:00,026
Break a man's nose.
Now, then...

932
01:19:04,448 --> 01:19:06,408
I'm afraid he will
never make a boxer.

933
01:19:06,492 --> 01:19:08,785
No aptitude
for knowledge.

934
01:19:10,496 --> 01:19:13,998
[Whistle Blowing]

935
01:19:21,132 --> 01:19:23,049
[Bell Clanging]

936
01:19:45,281 --> 01:19:48,324
Mr. Gruffydd!

937
01:20:25,905 --> 01:20:29,407
Ivor fell under a tram,
lower level.

938
01:20:47,259 --> 01:20:49,219
[Crying]

939
01:21:36,892 --> 01:21:38,476
Ivor!

940
01:21:51,490 --> 01:21:53,449
[Praying in Welsh]

941
01:22:23,439 --> 01:22:25,982
We have our first
grandson, Gwil.

942
01:22:26,066 --> 01:22:27,692
Give one
and take the other.

943
01:22:27,818 --> 01:22:30,486
Tell that to that
girl up there!
She'll have an answer for you.

944
01:22:30,571 --> 01:22:32,322
Do not kindle
the wrath.

945
01:22:32,406 --> 01:22:33,990
To hell with the wrath!

946
01:22:34,074 --> 01:22:36,659
And I'm saying it
plain to be heard.

947
01:22:42,416 --> 01:22:44,083
Ah, 'tis good.

948
01:22:44,168 --> 01:22:45,585
With honors, then.

949
01:22:45,669 --> 01:22:47,462
Our son is a scholar.

950
01:22:49,340 --> 01:22:51,049
What is it, Huw?

951
01:22:51,133 --> 01:22:52,508
I can't make
sense with it.

952
01:22:52,593 --> 01:22:53,676
Latin it is.

953
01:22:53,761 --> 01:22:57,055
Latin, is it? Why not good
Welsh or even English?

954
01:22:59,058 --> 01:23:00,183
It is the fashion.

955
01:23:00,601 --> 01:23:04,687
Fashion.
Frenchies, decimal points,
and bathtubs full of holes.

956
01:23:05,105 --> 01:23:07,857
My poor Huw,
they've stuffed
your head with Latin.

957
01:23:08,525 --> 01:23:11,319
Beth, my old beauty,
you, a black eye, is it?

958
01:23:11,403 --> 01:23:14,238
Go ahead, shout!
Wake up the baby, then.

959
01:23:14,323 --> 01:23:17,283
There is beautiful.
The image of my father,
he is.

960
01:23:19,912 --> 01:23:21,704
What bloody nonsense.

961
01:23:25,250 --> 01:23:27,877
Now then, Huw,
what will it be?

962
01:23:28,587 --> 01:23:32,006
To Cardiff to school,
then the university

963
01:23:32,091 --> 01:23:34,759
to be a lawyer,
is it, or a doctor?

964
01:23:35,844 --> 01:23:37,845
Dr. Huw Morgan.

965
01:23:37,930 --> 01:23:40,515
Well, Uncle Huw,
that will be
something special.

966
01:23:40,599 --> 01:23:42,850
Yes, indeed,
with a lovely
horse and trap

967
01:23:42,935 --> 01:23:45,603
and a good black suit
and a shirt with starch.

968
01:23:45,688 --> 01:23:47,313
Oh, there is good,
my little one.

969
01:23:47,398 --> 01:23:50,775
Now then, a glass
of buttermilk for you
with all your knowledge.

970
01:23:52,444 --> 01:23:55,029
Yes, Mother,
and some of
Bron's shortcake.

971
01:23:55,114 --> 01:23:58,741
Oh, and my shortcake
is to be fed to the pigs,
is it?

972
01:23:58,826 --> 01:24:01,786
No, only I finished
yours yesterday.

973
01:24:01,870 --> 01:24:03,621
Today is
shortcake day
with Bron.

974
01:24:03,956 --> 01:24:08,251
I'm sorry, Huw,
only currant bread
I made today.

975
01:24:08,335 --> 01:24:10,128
Nobody to eat it now.

976
01:24:21,515 --> 01:24:25,601
Oh, Mother,
I'm lonely without him.

977
01:24:25,686 --> 01:24:30,523
I put his boots
and clothes ready
every night,

978
01:24:30,607 --> 01:24:33,317
but they're there
still in the morning.

979
01:24:35,779 --> 01:24:37,572
There is lonely I am.

980
01:24:47,583 --> 01:24:52,420
Gwil, I will have Bron here
to live if she will come.

981
01:24:52,504 --> 01:24:53,796
Not Bron.

982
01:24:55,007 --> 01:24:57,049
One mistress
in the house.

983
01:24:59,928 --> 01:25:03,264
Now, Huw,
what will it be?

984
01:25:03,348 --> 01:25:06,184
I will go down
the colliery
with you, sir.

985
01:25:06,268 --> 01:25:09,937
Have sense, boy.
The colliery is
no place for you.

986
01:25:10,022 --> 01:25:12,148
Why not try for
a respectable job?

987
01:25:12,232 --> 01:25:13,816
Respectable?

988
01:25:13,901 --> 01:25:16,402
Are you and his brothers
a lot of old jailbirds?

989
01:25:16,487 --> 01:25:18,362
Leave it now, Beth.

990
01:25:18,447 --> 01:25:20,281
I only want
the best for the boy.

991
01:25:20,365 --> 01:25:22,366
If he is as good a man
as you and his brothers,

992
01:25:22,451 --> 01:25:23,785
I will rest happy.

993
01:25:23,869 --> 01:25:25,953
I'm thinking of
the boy's future.

994
01:25:26,038 --> 01:25:27,580
It was different
in our day,

995
01:25:27,664 --> 01:25:29,332
there was good money
and fair play for all.

996
01:25:29,416 --> 01:25:31,292
But Huw is a scholar.

997
01:25:31,376 --> 01:25:34,128
Why take brains
down a coal mine?

998
01:25:34,213 --> 01:25:36,005
I would rather, sir.

999
01:25:44,306 --> 01:25:45,640
All right.

1000
01:25:46,517 --> 01:25:49,519
Decide for yourself,

1001
01:25:49,603 --> 01:25:52,146
but blame yourself
if you are wrong.

1002
01:25:53,524 --> 01:25:55,191
The colliery, sir.

1003
01:25:57,736 --> 01:25:58,694
All right.
The colliery it is.

1004
01:25:58,779 --> 01:25:59,779
Good.

1005
01:26:06,578 --> 01:26:07,537
Where are you going?

1006
01:26:07,621 --> 01:26:09,080
To get drunk!

1007
01:26:12,751 --> 01:26:13,876
Bron?

1008
01:26:17,923 --> 01:26:20,049
I am going down
the colliery.

1009
01:26:20,133 --> 01:26:22,343
Oh, the colliery,
is it?

1010
01:26:23,929 --> 01:26:26,764
The old coal will be
shaking in its seam.

1011
01:26:32,437 --> 01:26:33,646
Bron...

1012
01:26:37,234 --> 01:26:43,030
Bro... Bron, would you have me
to live in this house

1013
01:26:43,115 --> 01:26:44,156
and have my wages?

1014
01:26:44,616 --> 01:26:46,325
Your home is
with your mother.

1015
01:26:46,410 --> 01:26:48,286
It was she who sent me.

1016
01:26:48,662 --> 01:26:49,662
From pity?

1017
01:26:50,080 --> 01:26:51,455
No, from sense.

1018
01:26:52,416 --> 01:26:54,959
If you put clothes
night and morning,

1019
01:26:55,043 --> 01:26:56,168
let them be
my clothes.

1020
01:26:57,629 --> 01:26:59,088
Good old man.

1021
01:26:59,798 --> 01:27:01,299
Yes or no, Bron?

1022
01:27:03,218 --> 01:27:04,385
Yes.

1023
01:27:04,469 --> 01:27:05,845
Goo... Good.

1024
01:27:06,972 --> 01:27:09,473
Good. I will
get my bed.

1025
01:27:15,898 --> 01:27:18,900
[Singing in Welsh]

1026
01:27:34,499 --> 01:28:34,892
[Whistle Blowing]

1027
01:28:43,527 --> 01:28:45,486
So it is a man now, is it?

1028
01:28:45,570 --> 01:28:47,363
And could I carry
such a man?

1029
01:28:47,447 --> 01:28:48,614
Lanto!

1030
01:28:48,699 --> 01:28:49,949
Ha ha ha!

1031
01:29:03,422 --> 01:29:04,839
5 shillings.

1032
01:29:07,676 --> 01:29:10,052
7 and tuppence.

1033
01:29:10,137 --> 01:29:11,679
Move along!

1034
01:29:11,763 --> 01:29:13,097
Thanks.

1035
01:29:13,849 --> 01:29:15,266
3 shillings.

1036
01:29:17,602 --> 01:29:18,769
2.09.

1037
01:29:20,230 --> 01:29:21,647
£1.02.

1038
01:29:24,317 --> 01:29:27,987
£2. 10.
Discharged, Morgan.

1039
01:29:30,198 --> 01:29:31,574
Move along.

1040
01:29:33,618 --> 01:29:37,121
£2. 10.
Discharged, Morgan.

1041
01:29:42,461 --> 01:29:43,627
£1. 10.

1042
01:29:56,808 --> 01:29:59,727
And so it came
to lanto and Davy,

1043
01:29:59,811 --> 01:30:03,105
the best workers
in the colliery
but too highly paid

1044
01:30:03,190 --> 01:30:06,025
to compete with poorer,
more desperate men.

1045
01:30:16,244 --> 01:30:18,162
[Bell Ringing]

1046
01:30:45,732 --> 01:30:48,067
Will you read us
a chapter, Father?

1047
01:30:48,151 --> 01:30:49,527
Yes, my son.

1048
01:30:52,948 --> 01:30:56,033
"The Lord is my shepherd,
I shall not want.

1049
01:30:56,118 --> 01:30:59,161
He maketh me to lie down
in green pastures.

1050
01:30:59,246 --> 01:31:02,123
He leadeth me
beside the still waters.

1051
01:31:02,207 --> 01:31:04,542
He restoreth my soul.

1052
01:31:04,626 --> 01:31:06,502
He leadeth me in the paths
of righteousness

1053
01:31:06,586 --> 01:31:08,754
for his name's sake.

1054
01:31:08,839 --> 01:31:11,465
Yea, though I walk
through the valley
of the shadow of death,

1055
01:31:12,384 --> 01:31:14,510
I will fear no evil

1056
01:31:14,594 --> 01:31:16,345
for thou art with me.

1057
01:31:16,429 --> 01:31:19,974
Thy rod and thy staff,
they comfort me.

1058
01:31:20,058 --> 01:31:21,976
Thou preparest
a table before me

1059
01:31:22,060 --> 01:31:24,520
in the presence
of mine enemies.

1060
01:31:24,604 --> 01:31:26,689
Thou anointest
my head with oil."

1061
01:31:26,773 --> 01:31:28,232
[Door Closes]

1062
01:31:37,450 --> 01:31:39,326
"My cup runneth over."

1063
01:31:55,177 --> 01:31:57,928
One line to Owen and Gwil,

1064
01:31:58,013 --> 01:32:01,182
down to Cape Town to Angharad,

1065
01:32:01,266 --> 01:32:04,643
over here to Canada to lanto,

1066
01:32:04,728 --> 01:32:07,730
and down here to Davy
in New Zealand.

1067
01:32:08,899 --> 01:32:12,776
And you are the star,
shining on them
from this house

1068
01:32:12,861 --> 01:32:15,487
all the way
across the continents
and the oceans.

1069
01:32:15,572 --> 01:32:17,531
All the way?

1070
01:32:17,616 --> 01:32:21,452
How far am I shining
if you can put it all
on a little piece of paper?

1071
01:32:22,579 --> 01:32:25,039
Now, a map it is,
my old beauty.

1072
01:32:25,123 --> 01:32:27,333
A picture of the world
to show you where they are.

1073
01:32:27,417 --> 01:32:30,544
I know where they are
without any old maps

1074
01:32:30,629 --> 01:32:33,130
or scratches
or spiders
or pencils.

1075
01:32:35,800 --> 01:32:37,635
They are in the house.

1076
01:32:59,032 --> 01:33:03,577
Then Angharad came
back from Cape Town
without her husband.

1077
01:33:03,662 --> 01:33:05,246
She did not come to us

1078
01:33:05,330 --> 01:33:07,790
but stayed at
the big Evans house,

1079
01:33:07,874 --> 01:33:10,209
her house on top of the hill.

1080
01:33:27,102 --> 01:33:28,811
To see Mrs. Evans,
please.

1081
01:33:28,895 --> 01:33:30,854
Who is it?
Huw Morgan.

1082
01:33:36,361 --> 01:33:38,112
Her brother, is it?

1083
01:33:39,698 --> 01:33:40,948
Come in.

1084
01:33:50,667 --> 01:33:52,042
Why, Huw...

1085
01:33:57,382 --> 01:34:00,759
Mrs. Nicholas,
will you bring
some tea, please?

1086
01:34:07,684 --> 01:34:09,435
Sit down, Huw.

1087
01:34:12,022 --> 01:34:14,398
There is grown you are,

1088
01:34:14,482 --> 01:34:15,983
and changed.

1089
01:34:16,067 --> 01:34:17,359
You, too.

1090
01:34:19,404 --> 01:34:22,906
I look ill and ought
to take care of myself.

1091
01:34:22,991 --> 01:34:25,951
Everyone coming in
the house says so,

1092
01:34:26,036 --> 01:34:28,412
so you say it, too,
and let us finish with it.

1093
01:34:29,122 --> 01:34:31,498
But tell me all the news.

1094
01:34:31,583 --> 01:34:32,875
How is...

1095
01:34:35,879 --> 01:34:38,088
How are all the boys
and girls we used to know?

1096
01:34:41,343 --> 01:34:42,760
Well,

1097
01:34:44,471 --> 01:34:46,722
the Jenkins girls
are married.

1098
01:34:48,058 --> 01:34:52,186
Maldwyn Hughes has
gone to be a doctor.

1099
01:34:52,270 --> 01:34:54,980
Rhys Howell is in
a solicitor's office,

1100
01:34:55,106 --> 01:34:57,983
and he's sending home
10 shillings a week.

1101
01:34:59,152 --> 01:35:01,737
And Mr. Gruffydd,

1102
01:35:01,821 --> 01:35:04,281
is still first up
and last to bed.

1103
01:35:06,409 --> 01:35:07,951
How is he, Huw?

1104
01:35:08,828 --> 01:35:10,329
Not as he was.

1105
01:35:12,707 --> 01:35:13,791
Is he ill?

1106
01:35:14,793 --> 01:35:18,128
Inside, in his eyes

1107
01:35:19,297 --> 01:35:20,923
and in his voice.

1108
01:35:23,968 --> 01:35:25,427
Like you.

1109
01:35:28,723 --> 01:35:30,557
Please go home, Huw.

1110
01:35:38,608 --> 01:35:39,566
I'm sorry.

1111
01:35:39,651 --> 01:35:41,693
Now then, Mrs. Evans.
Tea, is it?

1112
01:35:52,831 --> 01:35:56,166
Leave it,
Mrs. Nicholas.
I will pour.

1113
01:35:56,251 --> 01:35:58,001
Well!

1114
01:35:58,086 --> 01:36:01,505
I always did the pouring
for Mr. Lestyn's poor mother.

1115
01:36:02,966 --> 01:36:04,258
I will pour.

1116
01:36:05,051 --> 01:36:06,677
Yes, Mrs. Evans.

1117
01:36:10,515 --> 01:36:12,850
A new mistress
is like new sheets,

1118
01:36:12,934 --> 01:36:15,727
yes, a little bit stiff,

1119
01:36:17,355 --> 01:36:19,148
but washings to come.

1120
01:36:22,360 --> 01:36:24,820
Why do you
have her here?

1121
01:36:25,905 --> 01:36:30,367
37 years with the family,
or so she tells me
60 times a day.

1122
01:36:31,119 --> 01:36:32,828
Have some tea, Huw.

1123
01:36:32,912 --> 01:36:34,872
You don't
want me to go?

1124
01:36:36,166 --> 01:36:38,292
No. No, Huw.

1125
01:36:39,210 --> 01:36:41,628
I'm sorry
for being nasty.

1126
01:36:41,713 --> 01:36:43,172
Please stay.

1127
01:36:44,841 --> 01:36:46,258
Oh, Huw!

1128
01:36:46,342 --> 01:36:48,093
I tried to tell
Mother, but...

1129
01:36:48,178 --> 01:36:49,261
[Sobbing]

1130
01:36:54,225 --> 01:36:56,852
Not for me to say.

1131
01:36:56,936 --> 01:36:59,688
Only the housekeeper I am.

1132
01:36:59,772 --> 01:37:02,274
37 years in the family

1133
01:37:02,358 --> 01:37:04,776
and living to
curse the day!

1134
01:37:07,155 --> 01:37:09,239
It will not
surprise me any day

1135
01:37:09,324 --> 01:37:12,242
to see the old master
rise white from his grave.

1136
01:37:14,412 --> 01:37:17,539
'Tis only the gravestone
is holding him down,
I will swear.

1137
01:37:17,624 --> 01:37:19,917
Then what is it,
Mrs. Nicholas?

1138
01:37:34,349 --> 01:37:37,434
Divorce.

1139
01:37:38,311 --> 01:37:40,521
Divorce!

1140
01:37:41,064 --> 01:37:43,148
Saying nothing I am,

1141
01:37:43,233 --> 01:37:46,527
but that is what
is in her mind.

1142
01:37:46,611 --> 01:37:49,112
She is here without
her husband, is it?

1143
01:37:49,197 --> 01:37:50,781
And why?

1144
01:37:50,865 --> 01:37:53,951
'Tis because
she is in love
with this preacher.

1145
01:37:55,620 --> 01:37:58,038
Preacher, I said!
Mr. Gruffydd it is.

1146
01:37:58,414 --> 01:38:01,333
But Mr. Gruffydd has
not been near the house.

1147
01:38:01,417 --> 01:38:03,919
What difference
is that, girl?

1148
01:38:04,003 --> 01:38:05,879
Get on with your work!

1149
01:38:07,924 --> 01:38:09,883
We will not say
a word, Mrs. Nicholas.

1150
01:38:09,968 --> 01:38:10,926
Oh, no!

1151
01:38:11,010 --> 01:38:12,010
No, no!

1152
01:38:12,303 --> 01:38:13,470
Liar! Liar!

1153
01:38:13,555 --> 01:38:14,721
You're a filthy liar!

1154
01:38:15,848 --> 01:38:17,808
[Jeering and Shouting]

1155
01:38:20,645 --> 01:38:22,479
You're a filthy liar!

1156
01:38:25,608 --> 01:38:26,567
Come on!

1157
01:38:26,651 --> 01:38:28,235
Get him!

1158
01:38:28,319 --> 01:38:29,778
Come on, Roger!

1159
01:38:31,906 --> 01:38:32,906
Get him, Roger!

1160
01:38:32,991 --> 01:38:33,991
Let up!

1161
01:38:34,450 --> 01:38:36,201
Let me at him!

1162
01:38:39,205 --> 01:38:45,836
Liar! Liar! Liar!

1163
01:39:04,606 --> 01:39:07,441
As the slag had spread
over my valley,

1164
01:39:07,525 --> 01:39:11,528
so now a blackness spread
over the minds of its people.

1165
01:39:12,030 --> 01:39:14,031
For the first time
in my memory,

1166
01:39:14,115 --> 01:39:17,034
our front door was shut
tight in the daytime.

1167
01:39:35,136 --> 01:39:36,219
Dada?

1168
01:39:39,724 --> 01:39:41,058
Well, Huw,

1169
01:39:41,809 --> 01:39:43,477
trouble with the
philistines, is it?

1170
01:39:44,937 --> 01:39:47,689
Huw, what is it now?
Look at your hands.

1171
01:39:50,943 --> 01:39:52,361
Evan John,

1172
01:39:53,571 --> 01:39:57,783
he said things
about Angharad
and Mr. Gruffydd.

1173
01:39:59,744 --> 01:40:01,036
The children, too.

1174
01:40:06,167 --> 01:40:08,085
You were right, my son.

1175
01:40:20,014 --> 01:40:22,057
I will be back
for breakfast.

1176
01:40:22,141 --> 01:40:23,517
You will not
go to chapel?

1177
01:40:23,601 --> 01:40:24,768
No.

1178
01:40:35,196 --> 01:40:38,323
And if they
do this thing,

1179
01:40:38,408 --> 01:40:42,119
I will never set foot
in the chapel again
as long as I live.

1180
01:40:43,162 --> 01:40:45,914
I will have
the sheets warm
on your bed.

1181
01:40:48,042 --> 01:40:49,710
There is an old
beauty you are.

1182
01:40:49,794 --> 01:40:51,586
Go and scratch, boy.

1183
01:41:03,808 --> 01:41:06,476
What is this about
the chapel, Mother?

1184
01:41:07,603 --> 01:41:10,313
Tonight after
the service,

1185
01:41:10,398 --> 01:41:13,024
a deacons' meeting
over Angharad.

1186
01:41:13,109 --> 01:41:14,317
Angharad?

1187
01:41:14,402 --> 01:41:16,570
But she has
done nothing.

1188
01:41:16,654 --> 01:41:20,323
Nothing is enough for people
who have minds like cesspools.

1189
01:41:22,660 --> 01:41:24,619
Oh, Huw, my little one,

1190
01:41:25,747 --> 01:41:29,583
I hope when you're grown
their tongues will
be slower to hurt.

1191
01:41:31,794 --> 01:41:33,795
But will Angharad
have to be
at the meeting?

1192
01:41:33,880 --> 01:41:36,631
No, none of us
will be there.

1193
01:41:36,716 --> 01:41:40,051
But the disgrace
will not stay away.

1194
01:41:40,136 --> 01:41:41,803
I will go, Mother.

1195
01:41:45,057 --> 01:41:47,017
[Singing in Welsh]

1196
01:42:25,765 --> 01:42:29,559
This is the last time
I will talk in this chapel.

1197
01:42:34,232 --> 01:42:38,985
I am leaving the valley
with regret

1198
01:42:39,070 --> 01:42:42,989
toward those who
have helped me here

1199
01:42:43,074 --> 01:42:46,368
and who have
let me help them.

1200
01:42:50,164 --> 01:42:51,581
But,

1201
01:42:53,960 --> 01:42:55,752
for the rest of you,

1202
01:42:57,755 --> 01:42:59,756
those of you who
have only proved

1203
01:43:00,174 --> 01:43:04,386
that I have wasted
my time among you,
I have only this to say.

1204
01:43:05,805 --> 01:43:07,722
There is not
one among you

1205
01:43:07,807 --> 01:43:12,352
who has had
the courage to come to me
and accuse me of wrongdoing.

1206
01:43:12,436 --> 01:43:15,021
And yet, by any standard,
if there has been a sin,

1207
01:43:15,106 --> 01:43:18,108
I am the one
who should be
branded the sinner.

1208
01:43:19,861 --> 01:43:23,405
Will anyone raise
his voice here now
to accuse me?

1209
01:43:27,034 --> 01:43:28,076
No.

1210
01:43:30,162 --> 01:43:33,707
You're cowards, too,
as well as hypocrites.

1211
01:43:34,750 --> 01:43:36,626
But I don't blame you.

1212
01:43:37,879 --> 01:43:40,922
The fault is mine
as much as yours.

1213
01:43:43,050 --> 01:43:44,968
The idle tongues,

1214
01:43:46,137 --> 01:43:50,181
the poverty of mind
which you have shown

1215
01:43:51,392 --> 01:43:53,226
mean that I have failed
to reach most of you

1216
01:43:53,311 --> 01:43:55,896
with the lesson
I was given to teach.

1217
01:43:58,065 --> 01:43:59,149
Huw?

1218
01:44:01,819 --> 01:44:03,612
I thought,
when I was a young man,

1219
01:44:04,322 --> 01:44:07,198
that I would conquer
the world with truth.

1220
01:44:09,785 --> 01:44:14,080
I thought I would
lead an army greater than
Alexander ever dreamed of,

1221
01:44:16,834 --> 01:44:21,379
not to conquer nations
but to liberate mankind...

1222
01:44:22,298 --> 01:44:23,798
Yes, sir.

1223
01:44:23,883 --> 01:44:25,342
...with truth

1224
01:44:26,677 --> 01:44:28,845
and the golden
sound of the word.

1225
01:44:30,848 --> 01:44:33,016
But only a few
of them heard.

1226
01:44:35,019 --> 01:44:37,187
Only a few
of you understood.

1227
01:44:38,648 --> 01:44:43,276
The rest of you put on
black and sat in chapel!

1228
01:44:43,361 --> 01:44:45,153
Why do you come here?

1229
01:44:46,697 --> 01:44:49,324
Why do you dress
your hypocrisy in black

1230
01:44:49,408 --> 01:44:52,494
and parade before
your God on Sunday?

1231
01:44:52,578 --> 01:44:53,912
From love?

1232
01:44:53,996 --> 01:44:55,789
No.

1233
01:44:55,873 --> 01:44:58,124
For you've shown
that your hearts
are too withered

1234
01:44:58,209 --> 01:45:00,919
to receive the love
of your Divine Father.

1235
01:45:02,546 --> 01:45:04,130
I know why you've come.

1236
01:45:04,215 --> 01:45:07,133
I've seen it in your faces
Sunday after Sunday

1237
01:45:07,218 --> 01:45:09,010
as I've stood
here before you.

1238
01:45:09,095 --> 01:45:10,804
Fear has brought you here,

1239
01:45:10,888 --> 01:45:13,723
horrible,
superstitious fear.

1240
01:45:13,808 --> 01:45:15,392
Fear of divine retribution.

1241
01:45:17,478 --> 01:45:20,063
A bolt of fire
from the skies,

1242
01:45:20,147 --> 01:45:23,316
the vengeance of the Lord
and the justice of God.

1243
01:45:26,904 --> 01:45:29,656
But you have forgotten
the love of Jesus.

1244
01:45:31,909 --> 01:45:34,035
You disregard
his sacrifice.

1245
01:45:36,038 --> 01:45:41,376
Death, fear, flames,
horror, and black clothes!

1246
01:45:42,169 --> 01:45:43,670
Hold your meeting, then.

1247
01:45:43,754 --> 01:45:47,674
But know if you do
this in the name of God
and in the house of God,

1248
01:45:47,758 --> 01:45:50,468
you blaspheme against
Him and His word.

1249
01:45:56,559 --> 01:45:57,600
Wait!

1250
01:45:57,852 --> 01:46:00,979
There is a meeting,
Master Morgan.

1251
01:46:17,121 --> 01:46:18,580
Well, Huw.

1252
01:46:19,999 --> 01:46:22,083
I'm glad you've come.

1253
01:46:22,168 --> 01:46:24,210
Thank you, sir.

1254
01:46:24,295 --> 01:46:25,795
Is there
anything I can do?

1255
01:46:26,964 --> 01:46:29,382
Indeed there is.

1256
01:46:29,467 --> 01:46:31,718
You can do me
a great service.

1257
01:46:33,512 --> 01:46:34,888
This watch,

1258
01:46:36,140 --> 01:46:39,476
my father gave it to me
when I entered the ministry.

1259
01:46:40,561 --> 01:46:42,937
It's marked time
we both loved.

1260
01:46:44,565 --> 01:46:46,107
Take it.

1261
01:46:46,192 --> 01:46:47,609
Oh, no, sir.

1262
01:46:48,486 --> 01:46:51,446
A service I said
you'd be doing me.

1263
01:46:53,324 --> 01:46:56,576
No need for us
to shake hands.

1264
01:46:56,660 --> 01:46:59,370
We will live in
the minds of each other.

1265
01:47:03,334 --> 01:47:05,043
Mr. Gruffydd,

1266
01:47:05,127 --> 01:47:08,755
won't you see
Angharad before you go?

1267
01:47:08,839 --> 01:47:10,507
She wants you to.

1268
01:47:15,429 --> 01:47:16,471
No.

1269
01:47:18,724 --> 01:47:21,267
If I were to
see her again,

1270
01:47:23,354 --> 01:47:25,772
I couldn't find the
strength to leave her.

1271
01:47:30,361 --> 01:47:32,612
Goodbye, Huw.

1272
01:47:32,696 --> 01:47:35,198
And there's a good
old man you are.

1273
01:47:37,034 --> 01:47:40,120
[Whistle Blowing]

1274
01:47:51,382 --> 01:47:52,882
[Crowd Shouting]

1275
01:48:01,433 --> 01:48:02,600
What is it now?

1276
01:48:02,685 --> 01:48:04,269
Fire or flood or what?

1277
01:48:04,353 --> 01:48:06,271
Cave-in, they're saying.

1278
01:48:06,397 --> 01:48:07,397
Take me up by there.

1279
01:48:08,524 --> 01:48:10,775
What good in
the darkness of a mine?

1280
01:48:10,860 --> 01:48:12,569
Your eyes are no longer
good in the daylight

1281
01:48:12,653 --> 01:48:14,571
from the blows you
have taken in the ring.

1282
01:48:14,655 --> 01:48:17,073
I can still swing a pick
deeper than any man.

1283
01:48:17,158 --> 01:48:18,783
Take me up there.

1284
01:48:19,785 --> 01:48:21,244
[Explosion]

1285
01:48:23,873 --> 01:48:25,290
[Whistle Blowing]

1286
01:48:57,198 --> 01:49:00,116
Bron! Bron! Gwilym!

1287
01:49:00,201 --> 01:49:02,118
Those of you
with relatives.

1288
01:49:02,203 --> 01:49:03,953
Let them to the pit.

1289
01:49:09,293 --> 01:49:10,335
Gwilym Morgan?

1290
01:49:10,419 --> 01:49:11,461
Not yet, sir.

1291
01:49:11,545 --> 01:49:14,297
Mr. Gruffydd,
on the lower level he was.

1292
01:49:24,516 --> 01:49:25,975
[Coughing]

1293
01:49:48,165 --> 01:49:49,123
My father?

1294
01:49:49,208 --> 01:49:50,708
Not yet, Mrs. Evans.

1295
01:50:21,699 --> 01:50:23,574
[Crying]

1296
01:50:30,499 --> 01:50:32,000
[Woman Screams]

1297
01:50:35,546 --> 01:50:37,547
[Crying and Moaning]

1298
01:50:56,775 --> 01:50:58,234
[Church Bell Ringing]

1299
01:51:04,241 --> 01:51:05,700
Angharad.

1300
01:51:16,920 --> 01:51:19,422
Who is for Gwilym Morgan
and the others?

1301
01:51:20,090 --> 01:51:21,549
I, for one.

1302
01:51:21,633 --> 01:51:23,801
He is the blood
of my heart.

1303
01:51:25,721 --> 01:51:27,263
Come, Cyfartha.

1304
01:51:28,057 --> 01:51:30,516
'Tis a coward I am,

1305
01:51:30,601 --> 01:51:32,602
but I will hold
your coat.

1306
01:51:57,294 --> 01:51:59,253
[Singing in Welsh]

1307
01:52:56,019 --> 01:52:58,771
Dada!

1308
01:52:58,856 --> 01:53:05,361
[Echoing] Dada! Dada!

1309
01:53:35,225 --> 01:53:55,077
Dada!

1310
01:54:01,043 --> 01:54:02,126
Huw.

1311
01:54:02,211 --> 01:54:03,252
Lad.

1312
01:54:18,060 --> 01:54:19,769
Dada! Dada!

1313
01:54:49,716 --> 01:54:50,758
Dada!

1314
01:54:51,385 --> 01:54:52,552
Huw.

1315
01:54:52,636 --> 01:54:56,305
Dada.

1316
01:54:56,390 --> 01:54:58,099
Mr. Gruffydd!

1317
01:55:05,732 --> 01:55:08,818
There's a good
old man you are.

1318
01:55:17,411 --> 01:55:20,496
He came to me just now.

1319
01:55:20,581 --> 01:55:22,248
Ivor was with him.

1320
01:55:24,126 --> 01:55:26,377
He spoke to me

1321
01:55:26,461 --> 01:55:29,088
and told me of
the glory he had seen.

1322
01:55:44,938 --> 01:55:46,022
Look.

1323
01:55:49,318 --> 01:55:50,776
[Church Bell Ringing]

1324
01:55:50,861 --> 01:55:52,820
[Singing in Welsh]

1325
01:56:36,782 --> 01:56:40,076
Men like my father cannot die.

1326
01:56:40,160 --> 01:56:41,869
They are with me still,

1327
01:56:41,953 --> 01:56:45,331
real in memory
as they were in flesh,

1328
01:56:45,415 --> 01:56:47,708
loving and beloved forever.

1329
01:56:48,377 --> 01:56:50,211
How green was my valley then.

1330
01:56:51,088 --> 01:56:53,214
[Singing in Welsh]

1331
01:57:37,259 --> 01:57:39,218
[Church Bell Ringing}

1332
01:58:29,936 --> 01:58:30,936
ENGLISH - US - PSDH

